body.name: OKD Bathroom Floor Cabinet, Farmhouse Storage Cabinet with Sliding Barn Door & Storage Drawers, Small Storage Cabinet for Bathroom, Kitchen, Living Room, Rustic Oak with Antique White
features: [CUSTOMIZED STORAGE SPACE] 23.5"L × 12"W × 32"H, Utilize the tabletop to store cleaning supplies of any height, open shelf and three storage drawers for small items. Also sliding barn door and adjustable shelf to suit your storage needs, creating an orderly life space without mess not only in bathroom

[FARMHOUSE RUSTIC STYLE] Crafted from high-quality engineered wood, our storage cabinet is designed with classic barn door, double cross pattern and weathered finish that gives a charming rustic feel. Redecorate the whole space with elegant metal decorations to add more deeper farmhouse touch for it

[STURDY SUPPORT] Comes with one sturdy support base and tipping restraint hardware, so you could fix this small cabinet to the wall and prevent it from wobbling or tipping over. Also, please make sure hardware is suitable for your walls before installing, as different wall materials may require different types of anchors

[WATERPROOF MATERIAL] Waterproof surface and anti-rust coated metal accent hinges are ready to be used in moisture environments and easy to clean dust off, which makes it really suitable for using in bathroom and guarantees a long-term use even around some humidity

[EASY ASSEMBLY] Step-by-step instruction and hardware pack are in one package with the item, every part has an own label for easy assembly and there is no need of any power tools. We are always ready at your service if you have any issues with our product before or after your purchase

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Directions were easy to follow and has ample storage with adjustable shelves. It looks just like real wood, blending in nicely with our rustic theme.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Cabinet was easy to put together and looks great installed. We purchased it with the matching base cabinet to use as a coffee bar in our kitchen. Holds plenty of mugs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Small, but nice.
reviews.reviewText: It's not spacious but it's what I was looking for. It's good quality for the money. It took me three days to assemble it but I must admit I only spent an hour to hour and a half each day. It was fairly easy to assemble but there are a LOT of small parts. When assembling it be aware that there are two sizes of dowels and you need to take the draw slides apart - the instructions aren't clear on that part. Overall I'm satisfied and would recommend if you're looking for a smaller piece of furniture. I'm using mine in the bathroom for additional storage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Time and patience
reviews.reviewText: We took our time and built this in two days. Lots of pieces and directions were pretty straightforward. All pieces labeled with numbers and letters which were helpful. Unit is sturdy and looks great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Extra Bathroom Storage
reviews.reviewText: This cabinet came in pieces, LOTS of pieces. I had my doubts as I unpacked the box. But EVERYTHING was there and the instructions walked you thru EVERY step of construction. With pictures to ensure everything was oriented correctly and neatly labeled pieces, the instructions guide you thru making this cabinet. Once completed, this cabinet makes the perfect addition to our bathroom. The style (farmhouse barn door) also fit perfectly with our house. We had searched all the local places and big box stores for something like this, found nothing. This is perfect. It hold 8 rolls of TP behind the barn door and some bathroom gels or shampoo. The drawers hold washcloths for weekly usage. It was a bit daunting at first, but it came together beautifully and looks great in our bathroom.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for what I needed it for
reviews.reviewText: I've always had an awkward space in my bathroom so while redecorating, I decided to fill it. This was perfect for the job. The dimensions are very accurate, all the parts and pieces were extremely well labeled, no damage to anything, and the finished product is stable and gorgeous. The only thing that could be a con is that the instructions have no words at all, just pictures. That being said, the pictures are extremely detailed and the parts are so well labeled that it was not an issue. A couple recommendations for anyone building it: 1, I know a lot of people skip anchoring to the wall, with this unit, I would 100% recommend not to skip that step. It's not heavy enough on its own to keep it stable by itself, especially when you open the drawer or cabinet. 2, be careful with tightening the screws. They are extremely cheap and strip easily. This is not a bash, if everything was top quality, it would cost 3x as much. But if using a drill, go very very slow. Overall, it looks and feels fantastic once put together. Much more expensive looking than what it cost. Would definitely recommend this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not spacious but functional
reviews.reviewText: Took me 4 hours to assemble. Not quite Swedish store quality, but nice. Fun piece, good form factor, nice design. Assembly takes patience. Be careful. Wood and fasteners can esily be overtightened and broken. Just snug will work. I recommend gluing with good wood glue where possible. Glue will make it sturdier in the long run.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very strong cabinet
reviews.reviewText: Firstly, this cabinet was the most well packed cabinet I have seen in a long time. Everything was packed and labeled well with padding throughout. All parts were clearly labeled and there was even a spare parts bag. The instructions were VERY clear and easy to follow for the most part. We’ll get back to that. Once assembled, this felt very strong. They even included glue for the dowels.The ONLY minor complaint was assembling the draws. Instructions were fairly clear but they left play in where you can put the screws for the rails. And didn’t show how to get the rails apart 100%. But easy enough to figure out. It was difficult to get all the draws in straight. 2 of the 3 were perfect with the bottom one just slightly off. Nothing concerning.I would definitely buy this again!!
